    "## Data Processing Version v2\n",
    "### 2025-0907\n",
    "\n",
    "Manual corrections were applied to the CSV metadata:\n",
    "\n",
    "AB_C\n",
    "B_CD\n",
    "Chain-order cases were manually normalized (e.g., DADA_MN, 4U6H_AB_E, 3NPS_A_BC).\n",
    "Canonical ordering follows light-then-heavy when both chains exist.\n",
    "Single non-antibody chains are treated as antigen chains.\n",
    "If HL is present, remaining isolated chains are assigned as antigens.\n",
    "\n",
    "4NM8_ABCDEF_HL: keep chain B.\n",
    "5DWU_HL_AB: keep chain B as antigen; remove one sample with a mutation mapped to chain A.\n",
    "4KRP_A_B: chain B is a nanobody. In TSV it is rewritten as 4KRP_A_CB, B is treated as heavy chain, and an empty C chain is added in sequence metadata."
   ]
